{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1783487568274,"sessionID":"ses_0bfe020b5ffeoZNo5CdAcudSTe","part":{"id":"prt_f40249990001MeeORWAGk4lZjf","messageID":"msg_f402494a10012rHRZpuvFr6Yr8","sessionID":"ses_0bfe020b5ffeoZNo5CdAcudSTe","snapshot":"215b0c6f0a3261356aeece25ad9fddf3907ab55e","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1783487580239,"sessionID":"ses_0bfe020b5ffeoZNo5CdAcudSTe","part":{"id":"prt_f4024c80d0010rH35vSm7GmT00","messageID":"msg_f402494a10012rHRZpuvFr6Yr8","sessionID":"ses_0bfe020b5ffeoZNo5CdAcudSTe","type":"text","text":"The loop will stop after 4 iterations: it clears the 3-iteration floor, covers all five research questions with source-diverse evidence, and the fourth pass only found one additive risk.","time":{"start":1783487580173,"end":1783487580238},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_07bd8548144c0c6a016a4ddc5c2d448191ba70d8b18138446c","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487921302,"sessionID":"ses_0bfe020b5ffeoZNo5CdAcudSTe","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_982U2VFtYD21OKEIS9gNeSEk","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-7/deep-research-config.json\n+{\n+  \"topic\": \"Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\",\n+  \"maxIterations\": 10,\n+  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n+  \"antiConvergence\": {\n+    \"minIterations\": 3,\n+    \"convergenceMode\": \"default\",\n+    \"stopPolicy\": \"convergence\"\n+  },\n+  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n+  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n+  \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n+  \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n+  \"progressiveSynthesis\": true,\n+  \"specFolder\": \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research\",\n+  \"artifactDir\": \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-7\",\n+  \"resource_map_present\": false,\n+  \"resource_map\": {\n+    \"emit\": true\n+  },\n+  \"createdAt\": \"2026-07-08T05:12:24Z\",\n+  \"completedAt\": \"2026-07-08T05:12:24Z\",\n+  \"status\": \"complete\",\n+  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n+  \"loopType\": \"research\",\n+  \"stopPolicy\": \"convergence\",\n+  \"stopReason\": \"converged\",\n+  \"executor\": {\n+    \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\",\n+    \"model\": \"openai/gpt-5.5-fast\",\n+    \"reasoningEffort\": null,\n+    \"serviceTier\": null,\n+    \"sandboxMode\": \"workspace-write\",\n+    \"timeoutSeconds\": 900\n+  },\n+  \"lineage\": {\n+    \"sessionId\": \"fanout-gpt55-fast-7-1783486518892-2qss01\",\n+    \"parentSessionId\": null,\n+    \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n+    \"allowedModes\": [\n+      \"new\",\n+      \"resume\",\n+      \"restart\"\n+    ],\n+    \"deferredModes\": [\n+      \"fork\",\n+      \"completed-continue\"\n+    ],\n+    \"generation\": 1,\n+    \"continuedFromRun\": null\n+  },\n+  \"reducer\": {\n+    \"enabled\": true,\n+    \"version\": \"1.0\",\n+    \"registryFile\": \"deep-research-findings-registry.json\",\n+    \"dashboardFile\": \"deep-research-dashboard.md\",\n+    \"strategyFile\": \"deep-research-strategy.md\",\n+    \"machineOwnedSections\": [\n+      \"key-questions\",\n+      \"answered-questions\",\n+      \"what-worked\",\n+      \"what-failed\",\n+      \"exhausted-approaches\",\n+      \"ruled-out-directions\",\n+      \"next-focus\"\n+    ]\n+  },\n+  \"capabilityMatrixPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json\",\n+  \"capabilityMatrixDocPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md\",\n+  \"runtimeCapabilityResolver\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\",\n+  \"reducerScriptPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\",\n+  \"pauseSentinelPath\": \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-7/.deep-research-pause\",\n+  \"archiveRoot\": \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-7/_archive\",\n+  \"migrationWindowDays\": 28,\n+  \"fileProtection\": {\n+    \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable-after-init\",\n+    \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n+    \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n+    \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n+    \"deep-research-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n+    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n+    \"research.md\": \"mutable\",\n+    \"resource-map.md\": \"workflow-owned\"\n+  }\n+}\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-7/deep-research-state.jsonl\n+{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\",\"maxIterations\":10,\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-07-08T05:12:24Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research\",\"artifactDir\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-7\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-7-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1,\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"openai/gpt-5.5-fast\"},\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"started\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-7-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:12:24Z\",\"artifactDir\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-7\"}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"normalized_topic\":\"validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop\",\"specPath\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-7/.deep-research.lock\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:12:24Z\",\"note\":\"Spec writeback was intentionally not performed because the detached lineage prompt forbids writes outside the lineage artifact directory.\"}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":1,\"iteration\":1,\"status\":\"complete\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"mode=research; target_agent=deep-research; execution=detached_fanout_lineage; state_source=deep-research-state.jsonl\",\"focus\":\"Structural merge layout and directional path coupling\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.82,\"noveltyJustification\":\"First evidence pass established the actual target layout and confirmed both path-coupling directions directly in code.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the proposed system-deep-loop target layout structurally sound?\",\"Are the forward and reverse path-coupling repair rules correct?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Is the proposed system-deep-loop target layout structurally sound?\",\"Are the forward and reverse path-coupling repair rules correct?\"],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:73\",\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:154\",\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:171\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:11\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:14\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/orchestrate-topic.cjs:14\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"f-001-layout\",\"title\":\"Target layout is coherent if runtime stays infrastructure-only\",\"summary\":\"The proposed layout keeps four workflow packets at hub level and nests former runtime under runtime/ with no mode-registry entry, matching the parent spec's out-of-scope rule against behavior changes.\"},{\"id\":\"f-002-forward-rule\",\"title\":\"Forward coupling rule is correct\",\"summary\":\"Runtime-to-workflows imports such as render-command-contract.cjs currently climb to a sibling deep-loop-workflows folder; after both trees move under system-deep-loop/runtime and system-deep-loop/shared, the hop count is unchanged and the deep-loop-workflows segment is deleted.\"},{\"id\":\"f-003-reverse-rule\",\"title\":\"Reverse coupling rule is correct\",\"summary\":\"Workflow packets importing runtime, such as deep-research reduce-state and ai-council orchestrate-topic, currently climb to sibling deep-loop-runtime; after nesting, runtime is one level closer under the hub, so the required repair is minus one hop plus runtime/.\"},{\"id\":\"f-004-graph-metadata\",\"title\":\"One graph-metadata file is necessary\",\"summary\":\"Current separate graph metadata has reciprocal deep-loop-workflows/deep-loop-runtime edges; the unified skill should drop those structural edges and fresh-author one system-deep-loop graph metadata.\"},{\"id\":\"f-005-live-state\",\"title\":\"Stage-0 quiesce remains load-bearing\",\"summary\":\"The target move includes runtime/database and observability artifacts, so preserving line counts/checksums and confirming no in-flight loop remains a real precondition, not paperwork.\"}],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Add runtime as a workflowMode\",\"reason\":\"The target layout explicitly treats runtime as infrastructure, not an invokable mode.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:169\"}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:12:24Z\",\"durationMs\":42000}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":2,\"iteration\":2,\"status\":\"complete\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"mode=research; target_agent=deep-research; execution=detached_fanout_lineage; state_source=deep-research-state.jsonl\",\"focus\":\"system-spec-kit tooling-borrow and command contract path repair\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.68,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Second pass confirmed the tooling-borrow spans both runtime and system-spec-kit and cannot be deferred to external prose migration.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Does the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow need same-phase repair?\",\"Are compiled command contracts/codegen part of the migration risk?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Does the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow need same-phase repair?\",\"Are compiled command contracts/codegen part of the migration risk?\"],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:11\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tsconfig.json:12\",\"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json:31\",\"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:18\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/check-contract-drift.cjs:38\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:15\",\"file:.opencode/commands/deep/research.md:9\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"f-006-tooling-borrow\",\"title\":\"Tooling-borrow repair belongs in structural phase 002\",\"summary\":\"runtime/package.json and runtime/tsconfig.json borrow system-spec-kit TypeScript tooling, while system-spec-kit test:council and vitest include globs point back into deep-loop-runtime tests; all four paths become wrong at move time.\"},{\"id\":\"f-007-artifact-root-borrow\",\"title\":\"artifact-root.cjs is another system-spec-kit dependency seam\",\"summary\":\"The runtime artifact-root wrapper reaches into system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs, so the move should verify this seam alongside package.json and tsconfig rather than assuming only test tooling changes.\"},{\"id\":\"f-008-command-contracts\",\"title\":\"Compiled command contracts must be regenerated, not hand-edited\",\"summary\":\"/deep:* command frontmatter invokes render-command-contract.cjs, whose sources and drift checker enumerate old deep-loop paths; migration must update sources and regenerate compiled contracts to keep hashes authoritative.\"},{\"id\":\"f-009-workspace-root\",\"title\":\"compile-command-contracts has an anchor-depth hazard\",\"summary\":\"The child plan already notes WORKSPACE_ROOT depth repair; this is correct because nesting runtime one level deeper changes __dirname-relative workspace anchoring even when string literals are also renamed.\"}],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Defer system-spec-kit test path updates to child 003\",\"reason\":\"The runtime move would silently remove system-spec-kit council test coverage if the globs are missed; this is structural, not external prose migration.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:90\"}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:12:24Z\",\"durationMs\":39000}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":3,\"iteration\":3,\"status\":\"complete\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"mode=research; target_agent=deep-research; execution=detached_fanout_lineage; state_source=deep-research-state.jsonl\",\"focus\":\"External reference migration and advisor corpus risk\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.48,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Third pass verified the broad reference surface and found plugin fail-open behavior that increases the risk of a missed path.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the reference migration stage complete enough across commands, agents, docs, plugins, and advisor corpus?\",\"Are field-scoped advisor-corpus changes necessary?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Is the reference migration stage complete enough across commands, agents, docs, plugins, and advisor corpus?\",\"Are field-scoped advisor-corpus changes necessary?\"],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/spec.md:58\",\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:71\",\"file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:83\",\"file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:2570\",\"file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:95\",\"file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/explicit.ts:105\",\"file:.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js:35\",\"file:.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js:75\",\"file:.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js:353\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"f-010-reference-surface\",\"title\":\"External reference migration is genuinely broad\",\"summary\":\"A live scoped rg count found 764 old-name hits across 77 files in commands, agents, advisor, plugin, GitHub/root README surfaces, consistent with the phase plan's claim that this is not a simple rename.\"},{\"id\":\"f-011-advisor-constants\",\"title\":\"Advisor has duplicated hardcoded merged-skill identity\",\"summary\":\"Python skill_advisor.py and TypeScript aliases.ts both hardcode deep-loop-workflows as MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID, while explicit.ts boosts /deep phrases to the same identity; these must update as a reviewed pair.\"},{\"id\":\"f-012-advisor-corpus\",\"title\":\"Advisor corpus requires field-scoped edits and rebaseline\",\"summary\":\"labeled-prompts.jsonl stores deep-loop-workflows in skill_top_1 fields for deep-loop prompts; changing label fields without altering prompt text preserves historical corpus meaning and supports accuracy comparison.\"},{\"id\":\"f-013-plugin-fail-open\",\"title\":\"mk-deep-loop-guard missing-path behavior is silent\",\"summary\":\"The guard plugin loads .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json and returns null on any read/parse error; the hook then skips mismatch checks when registry is null, and documented behavior is fail-open.\"},{\"id\":\"f-014-command-surface-freeze\",\"title\":\"Freezing /deep:* commands and agent names is still the right scope\",\"summary\":\"The problem is two skill identities for one family, not public command names. Renaming /deep:* or agent names would multiply the migration surface without resolving the identity split.\"}],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Blind repo-wide find/replace including prompt text and specs history\",\"reason\":\"Specs history is explicitly non-breaking history, and advisor prompt/corpus fields need different safety rules.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/spec.md:77\"}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:12:24Z\",\"durationMs\":46000}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":4,\"iteration\":4,\"status\":\"insight\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"mode=research; target_agent=deep-research; execution=detached_fanout_lineage; state_source=deep-research-state.jsonl\",\"focus\":\"Fallback-router wiring decision and convergence check\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.08,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Fourth pass mostly confirmed prior design; the only additive insight is to defer fallback wiring unless this research phase must remediate failed GLM replicas before merge execution.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Should fallback-router.ts be wired now for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback?\",\"Has the research reached legal convergence?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Should fallback-router.ts be wired now for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback?\",\"Has the research reached legal convergence?\"],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:80\",\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:58\",\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md:43\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:299\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:357\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:628\",\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:650\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"f-015-fallback-module-ready\",\"title\":\"fallback-router.ts is ready but unused by fan-out\",\"summary\":\"The router validates known targets, scope, cycles, and hop count and resolveFallback returns fallback or fail-fast routes, but live non-test references are only the module definitions; fanout-pool.cjs still terminates after same-model retry exhaustion.\"},{\"id\":\"f-016-fallback-not-merge-blocker\",\"title\":\"Fallback wiring should remain optional for the structural merge\",\"summary\":\"The parent spec explicitly scopes workflow behavior changes out of the merge and tracks fallback wiring as optional; wiring it into fanout-pool is real behavior work and should not block rename/nesting.\"},{\"id\":\"f-017-fallback-before-rerun\",\"title\":\"Wire fallback before re-running GLM-heavy research only if operator wants automatic remediation\",\"summary\":\"If failed GLM replicas must be auto-substituted before this research fanout is repeated, phase 004 should land first; otherwise manual MiMo redispatch remains acceptable because fanout-merge enumerates lineage directories.\"},{\"id\":\"f-018-convergence\",\"title\":\"Legal convergence reached after 4 iterations\",\"summary\":\"All five key questions have evidence-backed answers, source diversity includes specs, workflow YAML, runtime code, advisor code, plugin code, and package/test config, and the latest pass produced low novelty.\"}],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Treat fallback-router wiring as required inside phase 002 or 003\",\"reason\":\"It changes fan-out behavior and retry semantics, while 002/003 are structural/reference migrations.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:80\"}],\"convergenceSignals\":{\"rollingAvg\":0.413,\"madScore\":0.08,\"entropyCoverage\":1,\"compositeStop\":0.92},\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:12:24Z\",\"durationMs\":31000}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"totalIterations\":4,\"answeredCount\":5,\"totalQuestions\":5,\"stopReason\":\"converged\",\"qualityGuards\":{\"sourceDiversity\":true,\"focusAlignment\":true,\"noSingleWeakSource\":true,\"minIterations\":true},\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:12:24Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-7-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-7/deep-research-strategy.md\n+# Deep Research Strategy: system-deep-loop Merge Design Stress Test\n+\n+## Research Topic\n+\n+Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding `deep-loop-runtime` into `deep-loop-workflows` as `system-deep-loop`: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether `fallback-router.ts` should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n+\n+## Known Context\n+\n+- `resource-map.md` was not present at init; skipping coverage gate for a pre-existing packet map.\n+- The phase parent states the merge is structural/identity work, not workflow-behavior change, and explicitly keeps `/deep:*` commands and deep agents stable. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:80]\n+- Child 002 owns the physical `deep-loop-workflows` rename, nesting `deep-loop-runtime` as `runtime/`, internal bidirectional path repair, and the four-site `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:69]\n+- Child 003 owns external reference migration across commands, agents, docs, plugin/hooks/CI, graph metadata, and advisor corpus. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/spec.md:69]\n+- Child 004 is optional and operator-gated fallback-router wiring. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:42]\n+\n+## Key Questions\n+\n+- [x] Is the proposed `system-deep-loop/` target layout structurally sound?\n+- [x] Are the forward and reverse path-coupling repair rules correct?\n+- [x] Does the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow need same-phase repair?\n+- [x] Is the external reference migration plan complete enough across commands, agents, READMEs, plugin/hooks/CI, graph edges, and advisor corpus?\n+- [x] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired now for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback?\n+\n+## Answered Questions\n+\n+- Target layout is sound if `runtime/` remains infrastructure-only with no `workflowMode` entry and no nested `graph-metadata.json`. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:154]\n+- Directional path repair is correct: forward runtime-to-workflows imports keep hop count and delete the old segment; reverse workflows-to-runtime imports remove one hop and rename to `runtime/`. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:171]\n+- The `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow must land with phase 002 because it affects runtime typecheck paths and system-spec-kit council test coverage. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json:31]\n+- External migration is broad and advisor-sensitive; field-scoped corpus changes and rebaselining are required. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:101]\n+- Fallback-router wiring is useful but should stay optional unless the operator wants automatic remediation before re-running GLM-heavy fanout. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:90]\n+\n+## What Worked\n+\n+- Verifying phase plans against live code caught the correct asymmetric path-repair rule and avoided a naive \"everything is one level deeper\" migration.\n+- Separating structural migration (002), external identity migration (003), and behavior work (004) kept the merge design tractable.\n+- Checking plugin behavior found a subtle silent-risk surface: `mk-deep-loop-guard` fails open when its old registry path disappears.\n+\n+## What Failed\n+\n+- No pre-existing `resource-map.md` existed in the spec folder, so there was no prior packet coverage map to reuse.\n+- A single global grep count is insufficient to plan migration safely; categories need different rewrite rules.\n+\n+## Exhausted Approaches\n+\n+- Blind repo-wide find/replace was rejected because specs history and advisor corpus fields need different handling.\n+- Adding `runtime/` as a mode-packet was rejected as a category error.\n+- Making fallback routing a blocker for 002/003 was rejected because it is fan-out behavior work, not structural identity repair.\n+\n+## Ruled-Out Directions\n+\n+- Rename `/deep:*` commands and deep agents: out of scope and unnecessary for the identity split.\n+- Defer `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repair to child 003: would risk silent council-test coverage loss.\n+- Rely on `mk-deep-loop-guard` to catch a missed registry path: it fails open on missing/unreadable registry.\n+\n+## Active Risks\n+\n+- The OpenCode guard plugin's `REGISTRY_RELATIVE_PATH` must be updated and explicitly tested because missing registry read returns `null` and skips mismatch checks. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js:75]\n+- The advisor merged identity exists in both Python and TypeScript constants and should gain or keep a drift-guard after migration. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:2579]\n+- Temporary compatibility symlinks may mask missed references during the rewrite window; residual grep must run after symlink removal.\n+\n+## Next Focus\n+\n+Synthesis complete. Recommended downstream action: revise child 003 to add an explicit `mk-deep-loop-guard` fail-open verification item if not already present, then proceed with 002 only after the full fanout synthesis is merged.\n+\n+## Non-Goals\n+\n+- No code changes, renames, symlink creation, or migration edits in this lineage.\n+- No writes outside this lineage artifact directory.\n+\n+## Stop Conditions\n+\n+- Stop once the minimum 3-iteration floor is satisfied, all five key questions have source-backed answers, and a final pass finds low novelty with source-diverse evidence.\n+\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-7/iterations/iteration-001.md\n+# Iteration 1: Structural Merge Layout and Directional Coupling\n+\n+## Focus\n+\n+Validate whether the target `system-deep-loop/` layout and the bidirectional path-coupling repair rules are mechanically correct.\n+\n+## Findings\n+\n+1. The target layout is coherent if former `deep-loop-runtime` becomes `system-deep-loop/runtime/` infrastructure and not another mode packet. The child 002 spec lists the hub-level mode packets and a nested `runtime/` subtree, then states `runtime/` is infrastructure, not a `workflowMode`. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:154] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:169]\n+2. The forward coupling rule is correct. `render-command-contract.cjs` currently imports `../../deep-loop-workflows/shared/rollout/resolve-injection-mode.cjs`; after the runtime folder is nested under the renamed hub, both source and target move together and the old sibling segment should be deleted without changing hop count. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:11]\n+3. The reverse coupling rule is correct. `deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs` imports `../../../deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs`, and ai-council imports runtime council primitives with the same sibling assumption. After nesting, `runtime/` is one level closer, so these become two-hop hub-local runtime imports. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:14] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/orchestrate-topic.cjs:14]\n+4. One fresh `graph-metadata.json` is the right target. The current hub graph points to runtime as a dependency, and runtime graph points back to workflows; after unification those edges become internal structure and should not remain graph edges. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/graph-metadata.json:10] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/graph-metadata.json:18]\n+5. Stage-0 quiesce is not optional paperwork. The target includes runtime `database/` state, while the parent spec calls out in-flight loop/write-lock risk; baseline checksums and no running fanout/convergence processes are real safeguards. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:135]\n+\n+## Sources Consulted\n+\n+- `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md`\n+- `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/orchestrate-topic.cjs`\n+\n+## Assessment\n+\n+- `newInfoRatio`: 0.82\n+- Novelty justification: first pass established live code anchors for both coupling directions and confirmed the layout premise.\n+- Confidence: high for the path-repair rule; medium for exact file count because grep output was sampled/truncated.\n+\n+## Reflection\n+\n+- Worked: checking live imports made the asymmetric path rule concrete.\n+- Failed: a broad grep alone would not distinguish forward from reverse coupling.\n+- Ruled out: adding `runtime/` as a registry mode, because the target layout explicitly says it is infrastructure.\n+\n+## Recommended Next Focus\n+\n+Verify the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow and command-contract/codegen paths, because they are load-bearing and not covered by simple in-tree rename logic.\n+\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-7/iterations/iteration-002.md\n+# Iteration 2: Tooling-Borrow and Command Contract Repair\n+\n+## Focus\n+\n+Validate whether the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow and command-contract generation paths are correctly scoped into the structural migration.\n+\n+## Findings\n+\n+1. The tooling-borrow is bidirectional and must be repaired with the physical move. Runtime typecheck calls `../system-spec-kit/node_modules/.bin/tsc`, and runtime `typeRoots` points at `../system-spec-kit/node_modules/@types`. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:11] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tsconfig.json:12]\n+2. `system-spec-kit` also points back into `deep-loop-runtime` for council tests. `test:council` directly includes two runtime integration files, and the vitest config includes `../deep-loop-runtime/tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts`. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json:31] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:18]\n+3. `artifact-root.cjs` is an additional seam: runtime delegates artifact-root resolution to `system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs`. The phase plan's tooling-borrow table is correct, but execution should also smoke this wrapper after the move. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:18]\n+4. Command contracts depend on old paths through both renderer and drift checker. `/deep:research` shells to `deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs`, while the runtime compiler/drift checker enumerate `deep-loop-workflows` authority sources. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/commands/deep/research.md:9] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/check-contract-drift.cjs:38] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:15]\n+5. The plan's warning about `WORKSPACE_ROOT` depth repair is valid. Once `compile-command-contracts.cjs` moves under `system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/`, `__dirname`-relative workspace anchoring changes even if the old string literals are renamed correctly. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:73]\n+\n+## Sources Consulted\n+\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tsconfig.json`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/check-contract-drift.cjs`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs`\n+\n+## Assessment\n+\n+- `newInfoRatio`: 0.68\n+- Novelty justification: confirmed tooling-borrow spans runtime and system-spec-kit and includes both typecheck and test discovery surfaces.\n+- Confidence: high that these repairs belong in phase 002.\n+\n+## Reflection\n+\n+- Worked: reading package/test config showed the silent-coverage failure mode.\n+- Failed: no command-contract compiled manifest was read in this iteration; regeneration determinism remains a phase-003 verification item.\n+- Ruled out: deferring the system-spec-kit edits to external reference migration.\n+\n+## Recommended Next Focus\n+\n+Validate external reference migration and advisor corpus handling, especially non-obvious surfaces like plugins and routing constants.\n+\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-7/iterations/iteration-003.md\n+# Iteration 3: External References, Advisor Corpus, and Guard Plugin\n+\n+## Focus\n+\n+Stress-test the external reference migration scope across command surfaces, advisor routing, corpus fixtures, graph metadata, and the OpenCode guard plugin.\n+\n+## Findings\n+\n+1. The external migration is broad enough to justify child 003's staged plan. A live scoped count across commands, agents, advisor, plugin, GitHub/root README surfaces found 764 old-name matches across 77 files, excluding specs and build output. [SOURCE: command:rg-count:2026-07-08]\n+2. Advisor routing has duplicated identity constants. Python `skill_advisor.py` points `MODE_REGISTRY_PATH` at `deep-loop-workflows`, and later hardcodes `MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID = \"deep-loop-workflows\"`; TypeScript `aliases.ts` separately hardcodes the same merged identity. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:83] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:2579] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:109]\n+3. Explicit lexical boosts also encode the old identity. `explicit.ts` maps `/deep:start-research-loop` and related phrases to `deep-loop-workflows`, so migration must include scorer constants, not just graph metadata and corpus files. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/explicit.ts:105]\n+4. The routing corpus supports field-scoped replacement. The skill id appears in `skill_top_1` values for deep-loop prompt rows, while prompt text remains semantic training/evaluation material. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/routing-accuracy/labeled-prompts.jsonl:24] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/routing-accuracy/labeled-prompts.jsonl:41]\n+5. New risk: `mk-deep-loop-guard` fails open if its registry path is missed. It reads `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json`, returns `null` on read/parse failure, and the hook skips mode-mismatch checks when `registry` is falsy; the plugin explicitly documents missing/unreadable registry as fail-open. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js:35] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js:75] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js:353]\n+\n+## Sources Consulted\n+\n+- `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/spec.md`\n+- `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/explicit.ts`\n+- `.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js`\n+\n+## Assessment\n+\n+- `newInfoRatio`: 0.48\n+- Novelty justification: confirmed advisor duplication and surfaced the guard plugin's silent fail-open behavior as an actionable migration risk.\n+- Confidence: high that child 003 needs staged, category-specific migration and explicit advisor rebaseline.\n+\n+## Reflection\n+\n+- Worked: combining grep counts with targeted code reads separated volume risk from correctness risk.\n+- Failed: this pass did not inspect every README/agent duplicate; the stage plan's residual-grep exit gate remains necessary.\n+- Ruled out: relying on temporary symlinks or guard runtime behavior to catch stale plugin paths.\n+\n+## Recommended Next Focus\n+\n+Resolve whether fallback-router wiring should be a merge blocker, optional pre-rerun hardening, or deferred follow-up.\n+\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-7/iterations/iteration-004.md\n+# Iteration 4: Fallback-Router Wiring and Convergence\n+\n+## Focus\n+\n+Validate whether `fallback-router.ts` should be wired now for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback, and decide whether research has legally converged.\n+\n+## Findings\n+\n+1. `fallback-router.ts` is real and robust at the pure-function layer. It validates target existence, scope, cycles, and hop count, and `resolveFallback()` returns either `action: 'fallback'` with a target or `action: 'fail-fast'` with a reason. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:299] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:357]\n+2. The live fan-out pool does not call it. Retry handling in `fanout-pool.cjs` only requeues the same index while retryable and below `maxRetries`; once exhausted, it records `retry_exhausted` and settles the same lineage as rejected. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:628] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:650]\n+3. Wiring fallback is behavior work, not structural merge work. The parent spec declares workflow behavior changes out of scope and explicitly tracks fallback-router wiring as optional/operator-gated. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:80] [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:90]\n+4. Recommendation: keep phase 004 optional, but run it before any GLM-heavy rerun if the operator requires automatic substitution instead of manual salvage/re-dispatch. The current phase-001 plan's manual fallback remains viable because merge enumerates lineage directories after the fact. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/plan.md:107]\n+5. Convergence is legal after 4 iterations. The 3-iteration floor is satisfied, all five key questions are answered, source diversity spans specs, YAML, runtime code, workflow code, advisor code, plugin code, and package/test config, and this final pass produced only one additive recommendation. [SOURCE: file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md:113]\n+\n+## Sources Consulted\n+\n+- `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md`\n+- `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/plan.md`\n+- `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs`\n+\n+## Assessment\n+\n+- `newInfoRatio`: 0.08\n+- Novelty justification: mostly confirmed the existing phase-004 plan; the additive insight is the conditional recommendation to wire fallback before a GLM-heavy rerun only if automatic remediation is required.\n+- Confidence: high that fallback wiring is optional for the merge and should not block phases 002/003.\n+\n+## Reflection\n+\n+- Worked: reading the actual retry-exhaustion branch resolved the zero-caller ambiguity.\n+- Failed: no forced-failure test was run; this is research only and phase 004 owns that implementation evidence.\n+- Ruled out: making fallback wiring a hard dependency of the structural rename.\n+\n+## Recommended Next Focus\n+\n+Synthesize results and feed one concrete revision into child 003: explicitly test/update `mk-deep-loop-guard` because its stale path fails open.\n+\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-r