ry and must move with phase 002.\",\n+      \"sources\": [\n+        \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:11\",\n+        \"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json:31\"\n+      ],\n+      \"iteration\": 2\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"q-reference-migration\",\n+      \"question\": \"Is the external reference migration plan complete enough?\",\n+      \"answer\": \"Mostly yes, with one recommended emphasis: explicitly verify the mk-deep-loop-guard plugin path because it fails open if stale.\",\n+      \"sources\": [\n+        \"file:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:2579\",\n+        \"file:.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js:353\"\n+      ],\n+      \"iteration\": 3\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"q-fallback\",\n+      \"question\": \"Should fallback-router.ts be wired now?\",\n+      \"answer\": \"Not as a merge blocker. Keep phase 004 optional; run it before a GLM-heavy rerun only if automatic fallback is required.\",\n+      \"sources\": [\n+        \"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:628\",\n+        \"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:80\"\n+      ],\n+      \"iteration\": 4\n+    }\n+  ],\n+  \"keyFindings\": [\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"f-001-layout\",\n+      \"title\": \"Target layout is coherent if runtime stays infrastructure-only\",\n+      \"summary\": \"The proposed layout keeps four workflow packets at hub level and nests former runtime under runtime/ with no mode-registry entry.\",\n+      \"severity\": \"confirmation\",\n+      \"iteration\": 1,\n+      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:154\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"f-002-forward-rule\",\n+      \"title\": \"Forward coupling rule is correct\",\n+      \"summary\": \"Runtime-to-workflows imports keep hop count and delete the deep-loop-workflows segment after nesting.\",\n+      \"severity\": \"confirmation\",\n+      \"iteration\": 1,\n+      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs:11\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"f-003-reverse-rule\",\n+      \"title\": \"Reverse coupling rule is correct\",\n+      \"summary\": \"Workflow-to-runtime imports remove one hop and target runtime/ after nesting.\",\n+      \"severity\": \"confirmation\",\n+      \"iteration\": 1,\n+      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:14\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"f-006-tooling-borrow\",\n+      \"title\": \"Tooling-borrow repair belongs in structural phase 002\",\n+      \"summary\": \"runtime and system-spec-kit point at each other for typecheck/test discovery, so this is move-time repair.\",\n+      \"severity\": \"confirmation\",\n+      \"iteration\": 2,\n+      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:11\", \"file:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json:31\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"f-010-reference-surface\",\n+      \"title\": \"External reference migration is genuinely broad\",\n+      \"summary\": \"Scoped live count found 764 old-name hits across 77 non-spec/non-dist files in external surfaces.\",\n+      \"severity\": \"confirmation\",\n+      \"iteration\": 3,\n+      \"sources\": [\"command:rg-count:2026-07-08\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"f-013-plugin-fail-open\",\n+      \"title\": \"mk-deep-loop-guard missing-path behavior is silent\",\n+      \"summary\": \"The guard returns null when registry read/parse fails and skips mismatch checks; stale path can silently disable protection.\",\n+      \"severity\": \"risk\",\n+      \"iteration\": 3,\n+      \"sources\": [\"file:.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js:75\", \"file:.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js:353\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"f-015-fallback-module-ready\",